# 4. Create an abstract class Telephone with ring(), lift(), and disconnect() methods. Create another class SmartTelephone and demonstrate polymorphism.

## Code

```java id="3k9qwr"
abstract class Telephone {

    abstract void ring();

    abstract void lift();

    abstract void disconnect();
}

class SmartTelephone extends Telephone {

    void ring() {

        System.out.println("Ringing...");
    }

    void lift() {

        System.out.println("Call Lifted...");
    }

    void disconnect() {

        System.out.println("Call Disconnected...");
    }

    void camera() {

        System.out.println("Opening Camera...");
    }
}

class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Telephone t = new SmartTelephone();

        t.ring();
        t.lift();
        t.disconnect();
    }
}
```

## Output

```text id="8p1qvl"
